title: Use Environment Variables in a Jenkins Pipeline
tags: @zettel _method jenkins
roam-id: 54452c9e-e274-4ec5-a9fa-8f796a45b78b
type: text/markdown

``` groovy
pipeline {
    agent { label 'agent-java' }

    environment {
        VAR0 = 'something'
        VAR1 = 'another variable'
    }

    stages {
        stage('Hello') {
            steps {
                echo 'Hello World'
            }
        }
    }
}

```
